<H3> <TI>   Slovak Ministers Meet Kliridhis, Conclude Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0701113594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1000 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0701113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The talks between Cyprus and Slovakia in Nicosia 
aimed at developing bilateral relations, particularly 
cooperation in the area of trade, conclude today. Cyprus and 
Slovakia are also interested in developing cooperation through 
European international organizations on security issues. Slovak 
Foreign Minister Jozef Moravcik and Economic Minister Jan Ducky 
met this morning with President Glavkos Kliridhis. Later they 
had separate meetings with Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis 
and Finance Minister Faidhros Oikonomidhis. The Slovak 
ministers, who are leading a large delegation, will depart this 
afternoon. 

