<F P=100> CANADA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Canadian, Briton Held Hostage in Yemen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601151394 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 
1430 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0601151394 </F>
<F P=104>  Montreal Radio Canada International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Canadian, a Briton, and six Yemenis are being held 
hostage by tribesmen in Yemen. The Canadian has not been 
identified, but a Canadian diplomat in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, 
said it appears the hostages are being well treated and that the 
Government of Yemen is negotiating their release. The eight men 
work for an American oil company. There have been dozens of 
kidnappings of foreigners by tribesmen, who routinely want 
favors from authorities in exchange for their release. 

</TEXT>

