<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy to Gabon Arrested on Spying Charges </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601170694 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1502 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0601170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hamburg (DDP/ADN)-- Rainer Mueller, ambassador of 
the Federal Republic of Germany to Gabon, has been arrested on 
suspicion of spying for the former GDR state security service, 
according to a report in the BILD newspaper. According to 
information from the paper, Mueller, who was also press 
spokesman for the Foreign Ministry, worked for the Stasi on an 
"ideological basis"--and, therefore, free of charge--since 1974. 
Security authorities described the extent of betrayal as 
"considerable," the paper writes (Friday [7 January] edition). 
  Mueller went to Gabon as ambassador last spring. Although he 
has so far denied the charges, the arrest warrant is still in 
force. The investigations are continuing. 

</TEXT>

