<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Views `Paralyzed' Partners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701114094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1057 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0701114094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Stuttgart (DDP/ADN) -- Economic Affairs Minister 
Guenter Rexrodt (FDP) [Free Democratic Party] has criticized his 
CDU/CSU [Christian Democratic Union/Christian Social Union] 
partners in the Bonn coalition in unusually severe terms. 
Speaking at the Epiphany meeting of the Free Democrats in 
Stuttgart on Thursday [6 January], Rexrodt said that the Union 
is, like the SPD, "torn by internal divisions, blind in its 
populism, and incapable of taking unconventional decisions." 
Thus the CDU wants to "outdo the Social Democrats in the 
politics of redistribution of wealth." 
  Rexrodt added that the Union has "become paralyzed, 
cautious, 
anxious, and preoccupied with its different wings." The FDP has 
the unique opportunity "to put itself at the head of the 
movement which is fighting for the renewal of our economic and 
social order." Prosperity for all cannot be guaranteed with the 
traditional recipes. What is needed is a return to classical 
liberal ideas of a state based on the rule of law, market 
economy, and social responsibility. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

