<H3> <TI>   FDP Disavows Coalition Plans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701115494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1120 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0701115494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Stuttgart (DDP/ADN) -- Germany's Free Democrats 
are beginning the mammoth election year of 1994 without any 
definite coalition plans. "We will decide before each election 
whether, when, and which coalition intentions we have," FDP 
[Free Democratic Party] chairman Klaus Kinkel said at the 
Liberals' Epiphany meeting in Stuttgart. The FDP wants to be 
involved in determining the shape of the government after the 
Bundestag elections, Kinkel stressed. The FDP chairman said his 
party is aiming for "a double-figure" share of the vote. 
[passage omitted] 

