<H3> <TI>   Foreign Exchange Reserves Up by 3.4 Billion Francs </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0601165894 Paris AFP in English 1647 GMT 6 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0601165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, Jan 6 (AFP) -- The Bank of France's foreign 
exchange reserves increased by 3.4 billion francs during the 
last week of last year, according to information from the 
central bank's weekly statistics released on Thursday [6 
January]. 
  That made a total of 10 billion francs on December 30, 
against 6.6 billion on December 23. 
  The reserves plunged deep into the red last summer during 
the 
European monetary crisis. 

