<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Apologizes For Attacks on Germany </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601142194 Hamburg DPA in German 1345 GMT 6 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0601142194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Vienna/Moscow (DPA) -- In an interview with the 
Austrian magazine NEWS, Vladimir Zhirinovksiy, the right-wing 
extremist leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia 
(LDPR), has apologized for the insults and threats he uttered in 
Sofia against Germany. "If what I said was taken as insulting, 
then I am sorry," Zhirinovskiy said in the interview, excerpts 
of which were prereleased to DPA. He had been "misunderstood." 
Shortly before Zhirinovkiy made the remarks to which he refers, 
the German Government had refused him an entry visa. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

