<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Key Interest Rates Remain Unchanged </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0601131394 Hamburg DPA in German 1240 GMT 6 Jan 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0601131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Frankfurt/Main (DPA) -- The key German interest 
rates remain unchanged. The Central Bank Council of the German 
Bundesbank decided today in Frankfurt, at its first meeting in 
the new year, that the third key interest rate -- the securities 
repurchase rate -- will be left at its present level of 6.0 
percent for a further two weeks. 
  The discount rate has thus remained unchanged at 5.75 
percent 
since 21 October 1993. The Lombard rate remains 6.75 percent. 

</TEXT>

