<H3> <TI>   Leaders Preview NATO Summit; View Expansion, Bosnia </TI></H3>
<H4>   Juppe Meets Owen, Stoltenberg </H4>
<F P=102> LD0701182794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701182794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Everybody agrees that there is a need to reexamine 
the issue of the presence, and particularly the role, of the 
blue helmets in Bosnia. [French] Foreign Minister Alain Juppe, 
who wants NATO member countries to discuss this in Brussels on 
Monday [10 January], met today in Paris with the mediators, Owen 
and Stoltenberg, who have for months now been leading with 
difficulty the peace negotiations on the former Yugoslavia. 
They all agree that if a negotiated solution seems impossible, 
conclusions should be drawn and the current peacekeeping 
operation should be reexamined. 

</TEXT>

