<H3> <TI>   NATO's Woerner Free of Cancer After Three Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0901201594 Paris AFP in English 1926 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0901201594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn, Jan 9 (AFP) -- NATO Secretary General Manfred 
Woerner has won his battle against cancer after three operations 
and said he had a good chance to live, the Sunday weekly BILD AM 
SONNTAG reported. 
  "I have beaten cancer," Woerner told the paper. "Doctors say 
I have an excellent chance" to live. 
  The interview was published on the eve of a two-day summit 
meeting of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization in Brussels. 
  Woerner, 59, who was West German defense minister from 1982 
to 1988, said he was operated on for the third time in 
mid-December in Aachen, western Germany. 
  He underwent surgery for colon cancer in April 1992 and June 
1993. 

