<F P=103> LD1001130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hilversum Radio Netherlands </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Dutch Minister of Home Affairs, Ien Dales, has 
died suddenly at the age of 62. 
  Ms. Dales joined the left of center coalition government 
headed by Prime Minister Ruud Lubbers in 1989. In a word of 
praise for her work, Deputy Prime Minister Wim Kok spoke this 
morning of her courage in introducing controversial proposals to 
cut the costs of public health care. 
  The Dutch Minister of Justice, Ernst Hirsch Ballin, will be 
temporarily in charge of the Ministry of Home Affairs. 

