<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   31 `Terrorists,' 10 Soldiers Die in Southeast </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0901143594 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1430 GMT 9 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0901143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, Jan 9 (AA) -- Thirty-one terrorists from 
the outlawed separatist organization and 10 people from security 
forces were killed in clashes in southeastern Sirnak, Mardin and 
Siirt Provinces. 
  Emergency Regional Governor's Office told AA that 16 
terrorists were killed in operations in Dargecit township in 
Mardin Province, in Guclukonak township in Sirnak and Ormanardi 
village in Siirt Province and a first lieutenant was also killed 
during operations. 
  Fifteen terrorists were killed in clashes when they 
attempted 
to raid Sariziyaret and Okcular military posts in Sirnak and 
Siirt Provinces. 
  Four rockets and 14 hand grenades were seized after the 
clashes. 
  Nine people from security forces were killed during the 
clashes. 

</TEXT>

