<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Issues Statement on Afghanistan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0801074494 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
2100 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0801074494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Turkey has expressed deep concern about the 
resumption of the intensified armed clashes in Afghanistan which 
claim many lives and cause great destruction. Turkey says that 
it is a great misfortune for the friendly and brotherly Afghan 
people that clashes continue when domestic peace should be 
established and when all efforts should focus on rebuilding the 
country. 
  A Foreign Ministry statement on the issue says Turkey 
insistently defends the need to establish a national [word 
indistinct] that will comprise all the groups in Afghanistan. 
It says: We urge all Afghan groups to stop this fighting among 
brothers and to make the necessary efforts to sign a lasting 
cease-fire as soon as possible. 

</TEXT>

