<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Reiterates Stance on Macedonia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0701194694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1800 GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0701194694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today 
referred to the priorities of the Greek presidency [of the 
European Union, EU]. At the same time, he reiterated that 
Greece does not accept any dialogue over the name of Skopje and 
added that it expects [Macedonian President] Kiro Gligorov to 
give practical proof of relaxing his intransigent positions. 
Among other things, the government spokesman said: 
  [Begin Venizelos recording] We will exercise this presidency 
while bearing in mind the Community's practices and the true 
correlations of forces being formulated within the framework of 
the EU's institutional bodies and while adhering to the goal of 
European integration. 
  Greece has already declared that it expects the Skopje 
government to follow some self-evident and fundamental dictates 
of international law. It expects the removal of national 
emblems that are Greek, an end to hostile and irredentist 
propaganda, and amendment of the preamble as well as Articles 3 
and 49 in the Skopje constitution. I repeat, these are not 
demands by Greece but obligations stemming from international 
law with which every state -- and moreover every UN member -- 
has to comply. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

