<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Rules Out' Secret Diplomacy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0801161094 Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA in Greek 8 Jan 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> NC0801161094 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] The government completely rules out any form of 
secret diplomacy on the issue of Skopje, but it is leaving the 
door open for a dialogue in case the Greek conditions are 
satisfied. 
  The government spokesman yesterday repeated that there are 
certain issues which are obviously open to negotiation and 
certain other issues which are not. The issue of the name is one 
of the issues not open to negotiation. He also said that "the 
government does not accept secret diplomacy." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

