<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government `Reportedly' Positive Toward NATO Initiative </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0801201294 Helsinki Radio Finland in English 1930 GMT 8 
Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0801201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Radio Finland </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Finland is reportedly prepared to give the 
western defense alliance, NATO, a positive response to its 
Partnership for Peace initiative. It is expected that on Monday 
[10 January] a NATO summit in Brussels will present a proposal 
on the issue to all the countries involved in the CSCE process, 
including Finland. According to a review prepared at the 
Foreign Ministry in Helsinki, the NATO initiative is in harmony 
with Finland's own foreign policy and security policy aims. The 
ministry is stressing, however, that Finland is not seeking new 
defense or security arrangements. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

