<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leotard on Critics `Undermining' Troops Morale </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701182894 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1700 
GMT 7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701182894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Defense Minister Francois Leotard, who was visiting 
the Landes testing center in Biscarrosse, rejected the call of 
some people for strong intervention in Bosnia. Francois Leotard 
wished that those who give advice to think first, particularly 
Abbe Pierre, to whom he said: 
  [Begin Leotard recording] Everybody understands that there 
is 
no military solution in Bosnia-Herzegovina. I have a lot of 
respect for Abbe Pierre. I cannot recall him being closely 
associated in recent months with any military decision that 
should be taken regarding this matter. Once more, all those who 
express themselves should think of not undermining either the 
morale or the action of our soldiers on the ground. One should 
be very careful. When we find ourselves in a crisis situation, 
youngsters, officers, non-commissioned officers, and soldiers 
are carrying out a difficult mission risking their lives. Every 
word should be weighed. I am not sure this has been the case 
during the last few weeks with civilians. We have to be very 
careful. We are engaged in sensitive operations. Let's not 
undermine either the morale or the missions our soldiers are 
asked to carry out. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

