<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council of Ministers Approve Employment Package </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0701190694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1756 GMT 
7 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0701190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Ministers has approved the so-called 
Giugni package. This is the legal decree containing a series of 
measures aimed at extending the framework in which social shock 
absorbers [money set aside for helping workers and communities 
through the recession] are applied. Further provisions have 
been added to the decree, concerning early-retirement for ILVA 
[Industry for the Production of Steel and Aluminium] and 
Alitalia personnel. 
  The Giugni package for employment plans to set aside 4.2 
trillion lire over three years; 1.6 trillion in 1994, and 1.3 
trillion in each of the next two years. 

</TEXT>

