<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSU Would Leave CDU Over Grand Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0901104994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0654 GMT 8 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0901104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DDP/ADN) -- The CSU [Christian Social Union] 
does not intend to take part in any grand coalition in Bonn in 
which the CDU is the junior partner. According to the news 
magazine FOCUS this was made clear by party leader [Finance 
Minister] Theo Waigel at the closed CSU meeting in Wildbad 
Kreuth. "There will be no grand coalition in which the CDU is 
junior partner with the CSU [Christian Social Union]. In that 
event, they [the CSU] will go over to the opposition," the 
Munich-based magazine quoted the party chairman as saying. 

</TEXT>

