<H3> <TI>   Calls For Nuclear Test Resumption </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1001102994 Paris AFP in English 1004 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1001102994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Paris, Jan 10 (AFP) -- France ought to resume 
nuclear weapons testing as soon as possible, Defence Minister 
Francois Leotard said here Monday [10 January], contradicting 
President Francois Mitterrand. 
  Speaking in a radio interview, Leotard said the precise 
reason for resuming tests was to acquire simulation techniques. 
[passage omitted] 

