<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mancini Cleared of Sisde Scandal Involvement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1001194194 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1837 GMT 
10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1001194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Interior Minister [Nicola] Mancino will not be 
investigated [as part of the Intelligence and Democratic 
Security Service -- Sisde -- slush fund inquiry]. The news was 
disclosed by Judge Ettore Torri at the end of the meeting which 
took place today in the Rome prosecutor's office. 
  Announcing the shelving of the case, Torri also said the 
files concerning statements made by former Sisde directors 
[Maurizio] Broccoletti and [Riccardo] Malpica will be sent to 
the parliamentary immunity committee. 
  The prosecutor's office also announced that he has no 
immediate plans to question Chief of Police [Vincenzo] Parisi. 

</TEXT>

