<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Reports on Confidence-Building Not Binding </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001124994 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1130 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1001124994 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis described 
the reports by the UN experts on the confidence-building 
measures as an aid to the United Nations, and reiterated that 
they are unofficial documents that do not bind the Greek Cypriot 
side. Kasoulidhis said the measures must be implemented in a 
way that will not directly or indirectly recognize the 
pseudostate. He said some of the points in the report will be 
discussed if and when the Turkish side replies positively to the 
three UN documents. The spokesman said: It would be a great 
diplomatic mistake to say that the Greek Cypriot side will 
negotiate the methods suggested by the experts, who will be a 
point for negotiating themselves. 
  Kasoulidhis said President Glavkos Kliridhis does not intend 
to convene the National Council to discuss the substance of the 
confidence-building measures or the reports by the UN experts. 
He concluded: The National Council discussed the tactics and 
strategy. 

</TEXT>

