<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnia Inaction Called `Most Shameful Cowardice' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1101130194 Paris AFP in English 1225 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1101130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Vatican, Jan 11 (AFP) -- The Vatican said Tuesday 
[11 January] the international community had committed "the 
crime of failing to help" end the war in the former Yugoslavia. 
  Europe was "dying" and a collective lack of action was "the 
most shameful cowardice," said the Vatican's Council for Justice 
and Peace, in an appeal made to mark a World Day of prayers for 
peace in the Balkans scheduled for January 23. 

</TEXT>

