<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Greece Reportedly Supports Cypriot NATO Membership </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1001181794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1001181794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Greece supports the membership of Cyprus in NATO if 
the U.S. plan for gradual expansion of the North Atlantic 
alliance toward the east is adopted. NATO expansion was at the 
center of discussions today, the first day of the NATO summit. 
  NATO leaders today approved a plan to establish closer 
military ties with all former communist countries in East 
Europe, including Russia. However, NATO leaders refrained from 
adopting a demand by many former East European countries to join 
NATO as equal members. The United States proposed a plan to 
gradually expand the alliance to the east. According to 
reliable Greek sources in Brussels, the Greek side is taking a 
positive approach to the U.S. plan but believes this expansion 
should include all CSCE members, in order to open the way for 
the membership of Cyprus. 

</TEXT>

