<H3> <TI>   Irishman Elected Vice President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1101162094 Paris AFP in English 1553 GMT 11 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1101162094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Frankfurt, Jan 11 (AFP) -- The governor of the Irish 
Central Bank, Maurice Doyle, was elected vice-president of the 
European Monetary Institute Tuesday afternoon [11 January] in 
Frankfurt, the institute announced. 
  It made the announcement after its first meeting. 
  The institute is the forerunner of a European central bank. 

</TEXT>

