<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry `Blackmailed' Into Releasing Neo-Nazi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1001162394 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 10 Jan 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1001162394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Stefan Schoeffel: "Attempt At Getting Kuessel </F>
Free"] 
  [Text] Vienna -- Last week, the Interior Ministry received 
a letter demanding the release of Gottfried Kuessel, who is 
serving a prison sentence for neo-Nazi activities. 
Investigations indicate that his conviction could be the reason 
for the series of letter bomb attacks [carried out last 
December]. 
  The unidentified blackmailers threatened to poison several 
people if their demands were not met. They demanded that a 
helicopter be placed ready and waiting at a field at 
Hennersdorf, south of Vienna, at 1:00 PM on Sunday [9 January]. 
Kuessel should be brought there direct from prison and taken 
away in the helicopter. His destination was not to be released 
by the blackmailers until immediately afterwards. 
  Police met most of the blackmailers' demands. They provided 
a helicopter and they also brought someone resembling Kuessel 
along to the helicopter, which took off at 1:30 PM. Yet, there 
was no sign of the blackmailers, whereupon police broke off 
their mission. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

